Three persons have survived a multiple road crash in Nnewi, Anambra State. The crash occurred at Afor Nnobi Market involving four vehicles, a truck, two tricycles and a motorcycle. The Nation gathered that the injured were rushed to hospital by sympathisers before the arrival of Federal Road Safety Corps officials. State Sector Public Education Officer, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Pascal Anigbo attributed the cause of the accident to speed limit violation. He said no death was recorded in the incident.